<section id="platforms-wide-section">
    <!-- Main Title with Theme Colors -->
    <h2 class="platforms-main-title">PROJECTS & <span class="highlight-platforms">PLATFORMS</span></h2>

    <!-- Vertical Container for the Stacked Cards -->
    <div class="platforms-vertical-container">
        
        <!-- Gotcha FOCUS! -->
        <div class="platform-card-wide">
            <h3 class="platform-title">Gotcha FOCUS!</h3>
            <p class="platform-desc-text" style="margin-top: 20px; font-weight: bold; color: #41D3BD; letter-spacing: 1px;">OBJECTIVES:</p>
            <p class="platform-desc-text">The platform aims to provide accessible and reliable academic support services by lending essential learning materials and student resources that help COS students succeed in their daily academic needs.</p>
            
            <p class="platform-desc-text" style="margin-top: 20px; font-weight: bold; color: #41D3BD; letter-spacing: 1px;">INCLUSIONS:</p>
            <ul class="platform-desc-text" style="text-align: left; padding-left: 20px; margin-top: 15px;">
                <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;"><strong>Reviewer Compilation:</strong> Aims to promote collaborative learning and make quality study materials more accessible, Reviewer Compilation will provide a centralized Google Drive containing reviewers contributed by students with their consent.</li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;"><strong>Calculator Lending:</strong> To reduce the financial burden of purchasing or replacing scientific calculators, Calculator Lending will provide students with temporary access to calculators for classes, laboratory activities, quizzes, and examinations.</li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;"><strong>Laboratory Gown Lending:</strong> To make laboratory classes more accessible and lessen the cost of purchasing personal laboratory gowns, Laboratory Gown Lending will provide reusable gowns that students can borrow when needed.</li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;"><strong>Booklet Lending:</strong> To ensure that students have immediate access to DLSU booklets when needed, Booklet Lending aims to assist students who may have forgotten to bring a booklet, are unable to purchase one due to limited availability, or cannot find a nearby place to buy one before class.</li>
            </ul>

            <p class="platform-desc-text" style="margin-top: 20px; font-weight: bold; color: #41D3BD; letter-spacing: 1px;">GOALS:</p>
            <ul class="platform-desc-text" style="text-align: left; padding-left: 20px; margin-top: 15px;">
                <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">Provide accessible academic support services that address the day-to-day needs of COS students.</li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">Improve student convenience by making essential academic materials readily available within the college.</li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">Promote equitable access to academic resources regardless of students' background.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    
        <!-- COS You Need to Know: ID 125 Consolidated Sheets -->
        <div class="platform-card-wide">
            <h3 class="platform-title">COS You Need to Know: ID 125 Consolidated Website</h3>
            <p class="platform-desc-text" style="margin-top: 20px; font-weight: bold; color: #41D3BD; letter-spacing: 1px;">OBJECTIVES:</p>
            <p class="platform-desc-text">The platform aims to provide a centralized and regularly updated information hub that enables COS students to easily access essential academic, administrative, and student-related information in one platform.</p>
            
            <p class="platform-desc-text" style="margin-top: 20px; font-weight: bold; color: #41D3BD; letter-spacing: 1px;">INCLUSIONS:</p>
            <ul class="platform-desc-text" style="text-align: left; padding-left: 20px; margin-top: 15px;">
                <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;"><strong>Contact Directory:</strong> A centralized directory containing the contact information of key university personnel and student leaders, including professors, department chairs, the dean and associate dean, academic advisers, and SCG officers.</li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;"><strong>Academic & Administrative Processes:</strong> A consolidated guide containing step-by-step procedures and requirements for common student transactions, including Leave of Absence (LOA), shifting, transferring, auto-enlistment (for certain courses), course dropping, course withdrawal, enlistment procedures, and pre-enlistment.</li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;"><strong>Academic Resources:</strong> A collection of important academic references that students frequently need throughout their stay in the university, including the Academic Advising Guide, curriculum flowcharts, Student Handbook FAQs and policies, Latin Honors guidelines, graduation policies, and retention policies.</li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;"><strong>Student Opportunities:</strong> A regularly updated compilation of opportunities available to COS students, including scholarships, college and university events, and student development opportunities.</li>
            </ul>

            <p class="platform-desc-text" style="margin-top: 20px; font-weight: bold; color: #41D3BD; letter-spacing: 1px;">GOALS:</p>
            <ul class="platform-desc-text" style="text-align: left; padding-left: 20px; margin-top: 15px;">
                <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">Centralize essential student information into one accessible and organized platform.</li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">Save students time and effort by eliminating the need to search across multiple websites, social media pages, and documents.</li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">Provide a reliable and sustainable information hub that is regularly maintained and updated to reflect current university policies and announcements.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- COSducational Assistance -->
        <div class="platform-card-wide">
            <h3 class="platform-title">MENTORchondria</h3>
            <p class="platform-desc-text" style="margin-top: 20px; font-weight: bold; color: #41D3BD; letter-spacing: 1px;">OBJECTIVES:</p>
            <p class="platform-desc-text">The platform aims to support COS students throughout their academic journey by providing accessible tutoring, mentorship, academic planning resources, and opportunities for research, internships, and career development.</p>
            
            <p class="platform-desc-text" style="margin-top: 20px; font-weight: bold; color: #41D3BD; letter-spacing: 1px;">INCLUSIONS:</p>
            <ul class="platform-desc-text" style="text-align: left; padding-left: 20px; margin-top: 15px;">
                <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;"><strong>Collaborative GWA Calculator and Course-Specific GWA Project:</strong> In partnership with the Science College Government (SCG), this initiative will develop an accessible GWA Calculator and course-specific academic planning tool that allows students to monitor their academic standing and project the grades needed to achieve their desired General Weighted Average (GWA) in a specific course.</li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;"><strong>Course Insights Forum:</strong> This will feature upperclassmen sharing their experiences in major and foundational COS courses through Focus Group Discussions (FGDs). Topics include course expectations, study strategies, laboratory work, assessments, and common challenges to help students prepare for upcoming terms and make informed academic decisions.</li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;"><strong>Professor-Endorsed Internship:</strong> Through coordination with the College Dean and faculty members, internship opportunities, research assistantships, and other academic openings endorsed by professors will be compiled and disseminated through FOCUS2025 platforms.</li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;"><strong>Tutoring Sessions:</strong> Tutoring Sessions will provide academic support for challenging courses commonly taken by COS students. Facilitated by qualified student tutors, these sessions aim to strengthen students' understanding of key concepts, reinforce classroom learning, and help them prepare for examinations and major assessments in a collaborative learning environment.</li>
            </ul>
            
            <p class="platform-desc-text" style="margin-top: 20px; font-weight: bold; color: #41D3BD; letter-spacing: 1px;">GOALS:</p>
            <ul class="platform-desc-text" style="text-align: left; padding-left: 20px; margin-top: 15px;">
                <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">Provide accessible academic support through tutoring, mentorship, and learning resources.</li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">Strengthen students' academic performance by helping them better understand challenging courses and concepts.</li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">Connect students with research, internship, and professional development opportunities to support their career growth.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
           
    </div>

    <br><br><br>

    <h2 class="platforms-main-title">LA <span class="highlight-platforms" style="color: #41D3BD">AGENDA</span></h2>

    <!-- Vertical Container for the Stacked Cards -->
    <div class="platforms-vertical-container">
        
        <!-- Committee on Student OUR Affairs -->
        <div class="platform-card-wide">
            <h3 class="platform-title">Committee on Student OUR Affairs</h3>
            <p class="platform-desc-text">A bill will be passed to establish a committee that will aid students and provide avenues in retrieving needed documents from the University Registrar.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Centralized College Grievance Channel -->
        <div class="platform-card-wide">
            <h3 class="platform-title">Centralized College Grievance Channel</h3>
            <p class="platform-desc-text">Through the College Legislative Board, an office under the College President will be established to handle grievances filed by students either within COS against professors or fellow students, forwarding them to the necessary authorities anonymously.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Improved Anti-Nepotism Bill -->
        <div class="platform-card-wide">
            <h3 class="platform-title">Improved Anti-Nepotism Bill</h3>
            <p class="platform-desc-text">To aid in combatting another type of nepotism, that being the appointment of officials based on friendship, a bill will be proposed in the LA to hold elected officials accountable for major appointments made without going through the proper processes, such as SGAR or similar appointment processes.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Amendments to the Anti-Disinformation Act of 2022 -->
        <div class="platform-card-wide">
            <h3 class="platform-title">Amendments to the Anti-Disinformation Act of 2022</h3>
            <p class="platform-desc-text">The flawed Anti-Disinformation Act takes all types of disinformation perpetrated by an officer, from inconsequential to slander, as equal; the proposed newer bill would categorize and punish accordingly such acts.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- CLB Members Bill -->
        <div class="platform-card-wide">
            <h3 class="platform-title">CLB Members Bill</h3>
            <p class="platform-desc-text">The College Legislative Boards of each college are too small and force those with legislative ideas for only the college to run for a university-spanning position in the Batch/College Legislator. This proposed bill would add new members to those boards elected similarly to the Batch/College Legislators.</p>
        </div>

    </div>

</section>

